# SingleCourseWebApp Template Documentation

This document provides a comprehensive guide to the template files in the SingleCourseWebApp Django application, including their relationships with JavaScript and CSS files. The data passed into these template files come from views.py.

## Template Structure Overview

The templates in this application follow a hierarchical structure:

```
course/templates/course/
├── adminpage/                # Admin interface templates
├── editcourse/               # Course management templates
├── homepage/                 # Home page templates
├── learningpage/             # Learning interface templates
│   └── lesson_types/         # Specific lesson type templates
└── submissions/              # Submission management templates
```

## Template-JavaScript-CSS Relationships

### 1. Home Page

**Template:** `course/templates/course/homepage/home.html`

**Description:** The main landing page for the course. Displays course information, enrollment options, and navigation to other parts of the application.

**JavaScript Dependencies:**
- `course/static/course/js/home.js`
  - `TabSystem`: Manages content tabs on the home page
  - `GroupManagement`: Handles joining and managing groups
  - `PopupManager`: Controls modal popups
  - `GroupSearch`: Provides search functionality for groups
  - `TicketSystem`: Handles support ticket creation

**CSS Dependencies:**
- `course/static/course/css/home.css`
  - Styling for the hero section
  - Styling for course features
  - Styling for tab system
  - Styling for group management popups

**Data Context:**
- `course`: Course object with details
- `is_enrolled`: Boolean indicating if user is enrolled
- `is_instructor`: Boolean indicating if user is an instructor
- `user_group`: Group object if user is in a group





